PineBridge Investments, the money-
management firm controlled by Hong Kong billionaire  Richard Li ,
appointed Arun Kumar as chief operating officer at its Middle
East unit.  Kumar was previously chief financial officer at Bahrain
Mumtalakat Holding Co. and worked at 3i Investments PLC and
JPMorgan Chase & Co., PineBridge Investments said in an e-mailed
statement today. Janick Fierens was appointed managing director,
head of client service.  Kumar and Fierens will be based at PineBridgeâ€™s Middle East
